1. Commercial Use — Prohibited

* Any form of commercial use is strictly prohibited.
* This includes, but is not limited to, selling, paid distribution, monetized redistribution, paywalled access, or inclusion in any service or product that generates revenue.
* Exceptions may only be granted with explicit written permission from the author.

2. Redistribution of Original Files — Restricted

* Public redistribution of the original, unmodified files is strictly prohibited.

* This includes uploading to websites, file hosting services, public repositories, forums, or any platform accessible to an unspecified audience.

* Private sharing is permitted only if ALL of the following conditions are met:
  a) The files are shared within a clearly defined and limited group (e.g., friends, team members)
  b) The files are not publicly accessible or indexed
  c) No payment, monetization, or indirect compensation is involved

3. Redistribution of Modified Versions — Conditionally Allowed

* Redistribution of modified versions is permitted only if ALL of the following conditions are met:
  a) There is any detectable difference in visual appearance, audio output, or in-game behavior (the magnitude of difference does not matter)
  b) All credit requirements defined in Section 4 are fully satisfied
  c) The distribution does not imply endorsement, sponsorship, or affiliation with the original author

4. Credit Requirements (Mandatory)

* The following information MUST be included in all cases:
  a) Original author name: “Pillusioner”
  b) Original source URL (download source of the original pack)
  c) A clear statement that the inherited parts remain under this license

* Credit MUST be included in BOTH:

  * assets/texts/credits.json
  * README file

* If no README file exists, assets/texts/credits.json alone is sufficient.

* Credit must be placed in a location and format that is easily visible and accessible to users.

* If the original source URL does not exist or cannot be verified, redistribution is strictly prohibited.

5. Media Usage — Allowed

* Use in videos, streams, screenshots, and other non-distributive media is fully permitted.
* Monetization of such media is allowed.
* Credit is not required but appreciated.

6. Scope of Application

* This license applies to:

  * All original files in this resource pack
  * Any extracted, edited, or repackaged versions
  * Any derivative works created from these files

* Any attempt to bypass these terms through superficial or technical modifications will be treated as a violation.

7. Server Distribution and Integration

* Direct distribution of original, unmodified files via servers (including automatic resource pack download) is considered public redistribution and is strictly prohibited.

* Integration into a server-specific resource pack is permitted only if ALL of the following conditions are met:
  a) The assets are modified
  b) Credit requirements defined in Section 4 are satisfied
  c) No implication of endorsement by the original author

* The following cases are considered unmodified:

  * File renaming only
  * Directory restructuring
  * Model reference changes only
  * Any case where the in-game result is completely identical

* Server access must be limited strictly to individuals who have been directly known or personally acknowledged by the server administrator.
  If participation is possible by individuals outside of this scope, it will be considered public distribution.

8. Definitions

* “Modified”:
  Any change that results in any detectable difference in visual, audio, or behavioral outcome

* “Unmodified”:
  Any asset that produces an identical in-game result

* “Functional Outcome”:
  The final visible, audible, or behavioral result experienced in-game

* “Public Distribution”:
  Any distribution method accessible to an unspecified or uncontrolled audience

* “Private Sharing”:
  Distribution within a clearly limited and controlled group

* “Commercial Use”:
  Any use that directly or indirectly generates revenue

* “Credit”:
  A display that satisfies all requirements defined in Section 4

